{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pizza dough","content":["Place flours, water, yeast, oil, salt and sugar into mixing bowl and knead <nobr>2 min\/<\/nobr>. Transfer into a large bowl, cover and set aside in a warm place to prove until doubled in size (approx. 1 hour).","Preheat oven to 220°C. Grease and line 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Divide dough into two portions. On a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface, roll out each piece of dough into an oval shape (approx. 35 x 25 cm), then transfer onto prepared baking trays. Pinch edges of dough to create a border, to help contain toppings during baking. Set aside while making toppings."]},{"title":"Roast beef and mushroom topping","content":["Place garlic into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add sour cream, ½ tsp of the salt and ¼ tsp of the pepper and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Spread mixture evenly over pizza bases.","Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh roast beef, whiskey and honey into it. Add ½ tsp salt, ¼ tsp pepper, sweet paprika and hot paprika and stir to combine well. Spread mixture evenly over pizza bases.","Place a separate bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh mushrooms into it. Add oil, ¼ tsp salt, ¼ tsp pepper, thyme and lemon zest, then stir to combine. Spread mixture evenly over pizza bases. Bake for 20-25 minutes (220°C). Sprinkle with spring onions\/shallots and shaved Parmesan cheese, before slicing and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pizza dough","content":["250 g spelt flour","250 g plain flour","280 g warm water","2 tsp dried instant yeast","20 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing","1 ¼ tsp salt","1 pinch white sugar"]},{"title":"Roast beef and mushroom topping","content":["1 garlic clove","300 g sour cream","1 ¼ tsp salt","¾ tsp ground black pepper","350 g roast beef, cut into thin strips (approx. 2 x 5 cm)","30 g whiskey","25 g honey","2 tsp sweet paprika","½ tsp hot paprika","250 g fresh brown mushrooms, cut into slices","1 tbsp olive oil","1 ½ tsp dried thyme","¾ tsp grated lemon zest, no white pith","2 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into very thin slices","50 g Parmesan cheese, shaved"]}],"id":"r253102","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-oX2ecJaGYyc\/XZQIB0ijl-I\/AAAAAAAAcOo\/sl6ha5rrTlkvWYwYKJsNV0-fvfYhE2JEQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_w6gW2rLrqdGBzbRB.png","title":"Roast beef and mushroom pizza","publishedAt":"2018-02-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{},"usefulItems":"baking trays (30 x 40 cm), rolling pin, large bowl, kitchen towel, silicone bread mat, bowl, baking paper, oven","basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 40m","8 portions"]}